# PicoRAM Tic-Tac-Toe  (computer-first, graphical OLED)
# Original Busch 58-word strategy (manual Part 2, p.4) preserved verbatim;
# full # grid (h-lines nudged to clear the O/X marks), spoken prompts.
# Keys: 8 9 A=top row, 4 5 6=middle, 0 1 2=bottom (maps to the 3x3 grid).
# Computer opens center. Says "YOU?" on your turn, "I WIN"/"DRAW" at the end.
# Set PicoRAM to TTS mode for speech.
